headline: Why Estée Lauder (EL) Shares Are Falling Today
summary: Shares of beauty products company Estée Lauder (NYSE:EL) fell 3.1% in the afternoon session after the major indices pulled back (Nasdaq -0.8%, S&P 500 -0.77%), largely due to escalating concerns surrounding the July 9th deadline for new US tariffs, now amplified by specific announcements.
